  "prompt": "What is the monarchy in the United Kingdom?",
  "response": "The monarchy in the United Kingdom is a constitutional monarchy, which means that the monarch's powers are largely ceremonial and symbolic, and the actual governance of the country is carried out by elected officials according to democratic principles. As of my last update in October 2023, the reigning monarch is King Charles III, who ascended to the throne following the death of his mother, Queen Elizabeth II, in September 2022. \n\nThe monarchy performs various ceremonial duties, represents the nation at home and abroad, and has roles in formal state processes, such as the opening of Parliament. However, legislative power rests with the Parliament, which includes the elected House of Commons and the appointed House of Lords, and executive power is exercised by the Prime Minister and the Cabinet. The monarch acts as a figurehead and symbol of the continuity and tradition of the British state.",
